topics.body:
. . . Ughh. . god damn it.

I hate to admit it and that, but right now conservatives have a point about something and chances are Whatevs right now is probably doing cheerleader backflips at being so right; the thing they're right about is the TPP.  Turns out why is the TPP a bad idea?  Simply put all the crap they've attached onto it would wipe out the middle class in the usa.  Sure it would increase the gross domestic profit of the usa, but the reason why it would is because it would nuke the middle class.


I know the analogy is a bit faulty, but you know how for decades in the usa factory jobs were in decline because they were all being outsourced to china and as a result countless individuals lost their jobs?  Similar situation.

Pros of the TPP:
Big businesses making more money
Cons of the TPP:
A fuck ton of the middle class in the usa will lose their jobs and have to get lower income jobs.
